<p>But how do we design better services:
</p>

<ul class="unordered-list">
  <li class="unordered-list__list-item">in areas with conflicting or competing priorities? 
</li>
  <li class="unordered-list__list-item">in areas with multiple leadership teams?
</li>
  <li class="unordered-list__list-item">with a reliance on politics?</li>
  <li class="unordered-list__list-item">across different competent authorities and government departments? </li>
</ul>

<p>When this is the case, hiring service designers into existing teams or structures won’t help us to change the things we design and build.
</p>

<h2>Defining design
</h2>

<p>Before we hire service designers we need to…
</p>

<ol class="ordered-list">
  <li class="ordered-list__list-item">Define what we mean by a service</li>
  <li class="ordered-list__list-item">Define the role of the service designer </li>
  <li class="ordered-list__list-item">Define the spaces in which service designers should work </li>
</ol>

